doc.after: Gyeongju is a major tourist destination for South Koreans as well as foreign visitors. It boasts the 1000 years of Silla heritage with vast number of ancient ruins and archaeological sites found throughout the city,[22] which help to attract 6 million visiting tourists including 750,000 foreigners per year.[5] The city government has parlayed its historic status into a basis for other tourism-related developments such as conferences, festivals, and resorts.[148]
